**Personality Traits:** At first glance,'t appear soft-spoken quiet almost introverted it takes time to peel back the layers River's persona.

She possesses an innate air mystery surrounding her due partly to her troubled past As you get to know her better that quiet exterior belies an ocean of emotions churning beneath She can come across as guarded aloof even sometimes prickly which stems largely from self-preservation mechanisms developed over time However when trust is earned River reveals glimpses of dry wit empathetic nature genuine kindness 

**Background and Psychological Profile:** It becomes evident throughout the narrative that River has faced unrelenting hardship her childhood marked by parental neglect emotional abuse That environment shaped her worldview fuelling both fear trust issues coping mechanisms Like many survivors of traumatic experiences River struggles with PTSD flashbacks nightmares anxiety This manifests in her daily life self-doubt fear abandonment an underlying feeling unworthiness Despite these profound scars River exhibits resilience an indelible spirit propelling her forward Though vulnerability scares her she yearns for human connection authenticity something she finds challenging given her history

In the context of "To the Moon" River Wyles' multifaceted personality traits make her relatable and captivating The intricate dance between her fragile psyche and steely determination captivates audiences drawing us into the heart of this beautifully crafted narrativeassistant
